# Data re-drive -- a Data line reached AFTER the tape's first
# render-reading command (Expect, Golden, or Click) updates the running
# binding set and RE-RENDERS: every Expect from that point on asserts
# against the NEW frame, not the one the tape opened with. Source is the
# same sample.ctml the core DSL example (sample_test.ctml) renders.

Source sample.ctml
Set Width 40
Data session.title "Welcome"
Data version "1.0"
Rows items 3

# Initial render: version 1.0.
Expect Text "Build 1.0"
Expect NotText "Build 2.0"

# Re-drive: version becomes 2.0 -- the tape re-renders from here on.
Data version "2.0"
Expect Text "Build 2.0"
Expect NotText "Build 1.0"

# A second re-drive, proving this is not a one-shot special case.
Data version "3.0"
Expect Text "Build 3.0"
Expect NotText "Build 2.0"

# A dotted-path bind (session.title) re-drives correctly too.
Data session.title "Goodbye"
Expect Text "Goodbye"
Expect NotText "Welcome"

# The row sequence built before the first render survives every re-drive
# unchanged -- re-drive is Data-only, Rows is not re-applied.
Expect Text "Row 1"
Expect Text "Row 3"
